<section xml:id="C5.S4">
<title>Special Values and Extrema</title>        
  
<subsection xml:id="C5.S4.SS1">
<title>Gamma Function</title>        
 
<para xml:id="C5.S4.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C5.S4.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="5.4.1" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E1">\Gamma\left(1\right)=1,n!=\Gamma\left(n+1\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C5.S4.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="5.4.2" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E2">n!!=\begin{cases}2^{\frac{1}{2}n}\Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}n+1\right),&amp;n\text{ even},\\ \pi^{-\frac{1}{2}}2^{\frac{1}{2}n+\frac{1}{2}}\Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}n+1\right ),&amp;n\text{ odd}.\end{cases</Math> } (The second line of Formula (5.4.2) also applies when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C5.S4.SS1.p1.m1">n=-1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C5.S4.SS1.p1.s3">
) <Math equation-number="5.4.3" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E3">|\Gamma\left(iy\right)|=\left(\frac{\pi}{y\sinh\left(\pi y\right)}\right)^{1/2},</Math> <Math equation-number="5.4.4" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E4">\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{2}+\mathrm{i}y\right)\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{2}-\mathrm{i} y\right)=\left|\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{2}+\mathrm{i}y\right)\right|^{2}=\frac{ \pi}{\cosh\left(\pi y\right)},</Math> <Math equation-number="5.4.5" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E5">\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{4}+\mathrm{i}y\right)\Gamma\left(\tfrac{3}{4}-\mathrm{i} y\right)=\frac{\pi\sqrt{2}}{\cosh\left(\pi y\right)+\mathrm{i}\sinh\left(\pi y \right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C5.S4.SS1.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="5.4.6" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E6">\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\right)=\pi^{1/2}\\ =1.77245\;38509\;05516\;02729\;\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="5.4.7" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E7">\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{3}\right)=2.67893\;85347\;07747\;63365\;\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="5.4.8" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E8">\Gamma\left(\tfrac{2}{3}\right)=1.35411\;79394\;26400\;41694\;\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="5.4.9" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E9">\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{4}\right)=3.62560\;99082\;21908\;31193\;\dots</Math> ,, <Math equation-number="5.4.10" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E10">\Gamma\left(\tfrac{3}{4}\right)=1.22541\;67024\;65177\;64512\;\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C5.S4.SS1.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="5.4.11" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E11">\Gamma'\left(1\right)=-\gamma</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C5.S4.SS2">
<title>Psi Function</title>         
 
<para xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="5.4.12" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E12">\psi\left(1\right)=-\gamma,\psi'\left(1\right)=\tfrac{1}{6}\pi^{2},</Math> <Math equation-number="5.4.13" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E13">\psi\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\right)=-\gamma-2\ln 2,\psi'\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\right)=\tfrac{1}{2}\pi^{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.s2">
For higher derivatives of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.m1">\psi\left(z\right)</Math> at <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.m2">z=1</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.m3">z=\frac{1}{2}</Math> , see §5.15.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="5.4.14" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E14">\psi\left(n+1\right)=\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{1}{k}-\gamma,</Math> <Math equation-number="5.4.15" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E15">\psi\left(n+\tfrac{1}{2}\right)=-\gamma-2\ln 2+2\left(1+\tfrac{1}{3}+\dots+ \tfrac{1}{2n-1}\right), if n=1,2,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="5.4.16" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E16">\Im\psi\left(iy\right)=\frac{1}{2y}+\frac{\pi}{2}\coth\left(\pi y\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="5.4.17" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E17">\Im\psi\left(\tfrac{1}{2}+iy\right)=\frac{\pi}{2}\tanh\left(\pi y\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="5.4.18" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E18">\Im\psi\left(1+iy\right)=-\frac{1}{2y}+\frac{\pi}{2}\coth\left(\pi y\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.s5">
If <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.m4">p,q</Math> are integers with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C5.S4.SS2.p1.m5">0&lt;p&lt;q</Math> , then <Math equation-number="5.4.19" mode="display" xml:id="C5.S4.E19">\psi\left(\frac{p}{q}\right)=-\gamma-\ln q-\frac{\pi}{2}\cot\left(\frac{\pi p} {q}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\sum_{k=1}^{q-1}\cos\left(\frac{2\pi kp}{q}\right)\ln \left(2-2\cos\left(\frac{2\pi k}{q}\right)\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
